There's a hole right here, but we'll come
back to that in just a minute.

00:00:30.729 --> 00:00:34.480
There's some wear on the rug, but I kinda
like that -- it has a wonderful sort of patina

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:35.480
to it.

00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:37.410
It can add some soulfulness to a room.

00:00:37.410 --> 00:00:41.410
Now, you can use an Oriental rug to be the
full rug for a room.

00:00:41.410 --> 00:00:46.170
Those are really expensive and hard to come
by, particularly if you have a large room.

00:00:46.170 --> 00:00:49.800
So what I like to do is use an Oriental rug
over another rug.

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:54.899
You can see here, I have a room-size rug that's
in sisal, a natural fiber.

00:00:54.899 --> 00:00:59.940
And what I'd like to do is lay this colorful,
old Oriental rug over it in a certain area.

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:06.140
Let me show you what I mean: For instance,
this rug is 6 1/2 by 16 1/2 feet.

00:01:06.140 --> 00:01:11.930
So if I measure it out, the rug will come
about middle way here, up to this point, under

00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:16.750
the sofa, and over here, and it will define
this sitting area that's focused on the fireplace.

00:01:16.750 --> 00:01:22.720
You see, I find that layering a rug on another
rug is a great look and a good use for these

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:26.910
Oriental rugs, particularly if you want a
seasonal change in a room.

00:01:26.910 --> 00:01:30.080
I don't plan to keep this rug in here throughout
the year.

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:32.010
I wanna use it in the fall and winter.

00:01:32.010 --> 00:01:37.190
It'll add a certain warmth both in terms of
its color and the fact that's a lovely wool

00:01:37.190 --> 00:01:38.190
rug.

